item.description:
So, earlier this month happened this popular event on the indie game dev community, LDJAM, basically you have a theme and 72 hours to finish an entire game based on it. This time around, the theme was &ldquo;One Room&rdquo;.
I thought to myself: &ldquo;OK! I got this!&rdquo;
No I didn&rsquo;t&hellip;
Presenting ROOM JUDGE(working title) - And how an apparent concrete idea can go wrong with lofty sense of scale and complexity&hellip; The idea: Making a game where you as the player would furnish the room and then, be judged from it.
